Detailed Description

Synchronize data classes with a device and computer.

Enumeration Type Documentation

enum mobilesync_sync_type_t

The sync type of the current sync session.

Enumerator:
MOBILESYNC_SYNC_TYPE_FAST 

Fast-sync requires that only the changes made since the last synchronization should be reported by the computer.

MOBILESYNC_SYNC_TYPE_SLOW 

Slow-sync requires that all data from the computer needs to be synchronized/sent.

MOBILESYNC_SYNC_TYPE_RESET 

Reset-sync signals that the computer should send all data again.

  ...

Add one or more new key:value pairs to the given actions plist.

Parameters:
actions The actions to modify.
Parameters:
... KEY, VALUE, [KEY, VALUE], NULL
Note:
The known keys so far are "SyncDeviceLinkEntityNamesKey" which expects an array of entity names, followed by a count paramter as well as "SyncDeviceLinkAllRecordsOfPulledEntityTypeSentKey" which expects an integer to use as a boolean value indiciating that the device should link submitted changes and report remapped identifiers.

mobilesync_error_t mobilesync_ready_to_send_changes_from_computer ( mobilesync_client_t  client  ) 

Verifies if the device is ready to receive changes from the computer.

This call changes the synchronization direction so that mobilesync_send_changes() can be used to send changes to the device.

Parameters:
client The mobilesync client
Returns:
MOBILESYNC_E_SUCCESS on success, MOBILESYNC_E_INVALID_ARG if one of the parameters is invalid, MOBILESYNC_E_PLIST_ERROR if the received plist is not of valid form, MOBILESYNC_E_WRONG_DIRECTION if the current sync direction does not permit this call, MOBILESYNC_E_CANCELLED if the device explicitly cancelled the session or MOBILESYNC_E_NOT_READY if the device is not ready to start receiving any changes

mobilesync_error_t mobilesync_start ( mobilesync_client_t  client,
const char *  data_class,
mobilesync_anchors_t  anchors,
uint64_t  computer_data_class_version,
mobilesync_sync_type_t *  sync_type,
uint64_t *  device_data_class_version 
)

Requests starting synchronization of a data class with the device.

Parameters:
client The mobilesync client
Parameters:
data_class The data class identifier to sync
Parameters:
anchors The anchors required to exchange with the device. The anchors allow the device to tell if the synchronization information on the computer and device are consistent to determine what sync type is required.
Parameters:
computer_data_class_version The version of the data class storage on the computer
Parameters:
sync_type A pointer to store the sync type reported by the device_anchor
Parameters:
device_data_class_version The version of the data class storage on the device
Returns:
MOBILESYNC_E_SUCCESS on success, MOBILESYNC_E_INVALID_ARG if one of the parameters is invalid, MOBILESYNC_E_PLIST_ERROR if the received plist is not of valid form, MOBILESYNC_E_SYNC_REFUSED if the device refused to sync or MOBILESYNC_E_CANCELLED if the device explicitly cancelled the sync request
